original: JANSSON, Johan Kuben, Handelsföreståndare, Falun, f Västland 23/11 92 av handl J J o Hildur Andersson. Realex Jönkp, hdls-sk. Anst v Kommanditbol Wilh Hanson & Co i Sthlm 15—20, Binger Co Symaskins AB 1 Sthlm 20—22, förest f Singers filial i Falun sed. 22. Sekr i Falu Missionsfrn, fd juniorledare o led av sommarhemsverksamh. NTO, Tempelriddare. Resor: Norge, Danm o Tyskl 37 o 38.
translated: JANSSON, Johan Kuben, Trading Manager, Falun, born in Västland on November 23, 1892, to merchant J J and Hildur Andersson. Attended Jönkp Real School, Commercial School. Employed by Kommanditbol Wilh Hanson & Co in Stockholm from 1915 to 1920, Binger Co Sewing Machines AB in Stockholm from 1920 to 1922, and since 1922 has been the manager of the Singer branch in Falun. Secretary of the Falu Missionary Association, former junior leader and member of the summer home activities of the Swedish Temperance League (NTO), and Templar Knight. Traveled to Norway, Denmark, and Germany in 1937 and 1938.
